(4, 5, 'SINGULAR AND PLURAL NAUN', 'singular-and-plural-naun', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Singular and Plural Nouns - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 1: STRUCTURE (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>A. SINGULAR AND PLURAL NOUN</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Singular noun</strong> merupakan kata benda yang menyatakan bahwa benda itu berjumlah satu atau tunggal, biasa dikenal dengan kata benda tunggal.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Singular noun means one person, thing, place, etc.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> Mother, Doctor, Supermarket, Student, Chair, Basketball</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Sedangkan <strong>plural noun</strong> merupakan kebalikan dari singular noun, ini merupakan kata benda yang menyatakan bahwa benda tersebut berjumlah banyak/jamak dengan makna lebih dari satu. Biasa dikenal dengan kata benda jamak.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Plural Noun means two or more than one person, thing, place, etc.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> Mothers, Doctors, Supermarkets, Students, Chairs, Basketballs</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Penggunaan dalam Kalimat</h2>\r\n    \r\n    <h3>1. Singular Nouns</h3>\r\n    <p>Pemakaian singular nouns sering diawali oleh kata sandang (article) <strong>“a”</strong> atau <strong>“an”</strong> dan <strong>“the”</strong>.</p>\r\n    <p>Dan apabila bentuk singular noun digunakan dalam bentuk kalimat, maka kata kerjanya yang digunakan adalah kata kerja tunggal, yaitu dengan menambahkan huruf <strong>“-s/es/ies”</strong>. Sedangkan kata kerja bantu menggunakan kata <strong>“is/was”</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The boy writes a novel.</li>\r\n            <li>My key is in your bag.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Plural Nouns</h3>\r\n    <p>Apabila bentuk plural nouns digunakan dalam bentuk kalimat, maka kata kerjanya harus berbentuk kata kerja plural, yaitu tanpa menambahkan huruf <strong>“-s/es/ies”</strong>. Sedangkan kata kerja bantunya dapat menggunakan kata <strong>“are”</strong> atau <strong>“were”</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The boys write some novels.</li>\r\n            <li>My keys are in your bag.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Forming Plurals Table</h2>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 1. Rules of Regular Singular and Plural Nouns</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>Rule</th>\r\n                <th>Singular Noun</th>\r\n                <th>Plural Noun</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>For most noun just add <strong>-s</strong></td>\r\n                <td>door</td>\r\n                <td>doors</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>If a noun ends in <strong>s, z, x, sh, or ch</strong> add <strong>-es</strong></td>\r\n                <td>boss<br>buzz<br>box<br>wish<br>bunch</td>\r\n                <td>bosses<br>buzzes<br>boxes<br>wishes<br>bunches</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>If a noun ends in a <strong>consonant</strong> followed by <strong>y</strong>, then change <strong>\"y\"</strong> to <strong>\"i\"</strong> and add <strong>-es</strong></td>\r\n                <td>berry</td>\r\n                <td>berries</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 2. Rules of Irregular Singular and Plural Nouns</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>Rule</th>\r\n                <th>Singular Noun</th>\r\n                <th>Plural Noun</th>\r\n                <th>Exceptions (Pengecualian)</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>If a noun ends in a <strong>vowel</strong> followed by <strong>y</strong>, add <strong>-s</strong></td>\r\n                <td>toy</td>\r\n                <td>toys</td>\r\n                <td>-</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>If a noun ends in a <strong>consonant</strong> followed by <strong>o</strong>, add <strong>-es</strong></td>\r\n                <td>hero</td>\r\n                <td>heroes</td>\r\n                <td>piano &rarr; pianos<br>memento &rarr; mementos</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>For nouns ending in <strong>f and fe</strong>, change <strong>\"f/fe\"</strong> to <strong>\"v\"</strong> and add <strong>-es</strong></td>\r\n                <td>shelf<br>knife</td>\r\n                <td>shelves<br>knives</td>\r\n                <td>roof &rarr; roofs<br>safe &rarr; safes</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>Some nouns change a few letters or complete spelling.</td>\r\n                <td>man</td>\r\n                <td>men</td>\r\n                <td>-</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>Some nouns are the same in both forms.</td>\r\n                <td>sheep</td>\r\n                <td>sheep</td>\r\n                <td>-</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-16 09:10:52', '2026-06-16 14:52:09'),
(5, 5, 'COUNTABLE AND UNCOUNTABLE NOUN', 'countable-and-uncountable-noun', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Countable and Uncountable Nouns - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 1: STRUCTURE (Part 2)</div>\r\n        <h1>B. COUNTABLE AND UNCOUNTABLE NOUN</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Countable noun</strong> merupakan kata benda yang dapat dihitung secara langsung menggunakan angka (satu, dua, tiga, dst.). Kata benda jenis ini memiliki bentuk tunggal (singular) maupun bentuk jamak (plural).</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Countable nouns are nouns that can be counted. They have both singular and plural forms.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> An apple, Two apples, A book, Three books, A cat, Many cats.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Sedangkan <strong>uncountable noun</strong> adalah kata benda yang tidak dapat dihitung secara langsung menggunakan angka karena sifat objeknya yang abstrak, berbentuk cairan, gas, atau terdiri dari partikel-partikel yang terlalu kecil untuk dihitung. Kata benda ini tidak memiliki bentuk jamak dan selalu dianggap tunggal.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Uncountable nouns are nouns that cannot be counted. They usually do not have a plural form.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> Water, Sugar, Rice, Money, Information, Happiness, Milk.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Penggunaan Kata Penunjuk Jumlah (Quantifiers)</h2>\r\n    <p>Dalam tes TOEFL atau pengerjaan kalimat bahasa Inggris, sangat penting untuk membedakan kata penunjuk jumlah yang mengikuti kedua jenis kata benda tersebut.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 1. Penunjuk Jumlah untuk Countable vs Uncountable</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>Kata Penunjuk Jumlah</th>\r\n                <th>Countable Nouns (Jamak)</th>\r\n                <th>Uncountable Nouns</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>Banyak</td>\r\n                <td><strong>Many</strong><br><em>(Many students)</em></td>\r\n                <td><strong>Much</strong><br><em>(Much water)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>Sedikit</td>\r\n                <td><strong>Few / A few</strong><br><em>(Few friends)</em></td>\r\n                <td><strong>Little / A little</strong><br><em>(Little time)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>Beberapa / Sejumlah</td>\r\n                <td><strong>A number of</strong><br><em>(A number of cars)</em></td>\r\n                <td><strong>An amount of</strong><br><em>(An amount of money)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>Lebih sedikit</td>\r\n                <td><strong>Fewer</strong><br><em>(Fewer options)</em></td>\r\n                <td><strong>Less</strong><br><em>(Less salt)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Ketentuan Penting dalam Kalimat</h2>\r\n    \r\n    <h3>1. Aturan Countable Noun</h3>\r\n    <p>Jika jumlahnya satu (tunggal), wajib menggunakan article <strong>\"a/an\"</strong> atau kata penunjuk tunggal lainnya. Jika jumlahnya lebih dari satu (jamak), wajib diubah ke bentuk plural (ditambah <strong>-s/-es</strong>) dan kata kerjanya menyesuaikan.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>I have <strong>a car</strong>. <em>(Singular)</em></li>\r\n            <li>There are <strong>many cars</strong> in the parking lot. <em>(Plural)</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Aturan Uncountable Noun</h3>\r\n    <p>Uncountable noun <strong>tidak boleh</strong> diawali dengan article <strong>\"a/an\"</strong> langsung di depannya, dan tidak boleh ditambahkan akhiran <strong>\"-s/-es\"</strong>. Kata kerja bantu yang digunakan selalu berbentuk tunggal seperti <strong>\"is\"</strong> atau <strong>\"was\"</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The <strong>information is</strong> very useful. <em>(Bukan: The informations are...)</em></li>\r\n            <li>He gave me some <strong>advice</strong>. <em>(Bukan: an advice / advices)</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Untuk menghitung benda yang tidak dapat dihitung (uncountable), kita harus menggunakan wadah, satuan, atau ukuran takaran penunjuk benda tersebut (*measure words*).</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example of Measure Words:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>A glass of water / Two glasses of water</li>\r\n            <li>A bag of rice / Three bags of rice</li>\r\n            <li>A piece of information</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 2, 1, '2026-06-16 09:17:03', '2026-06-16 14:52:21'),
(6, 5, 'SUBJECT AND OBJECT PRONOUN', 'subject-and-object-pronoun', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Subject and Object Pronouns - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 1: STRUCTURE (Part 3)</div>\r\n        <h1>C. SUBJECT AND OBJECT PRONOUNS</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Subject pronoun</strong> adalah kata ganti yang berfungsi sebagai pelaku (subjek) dalam sebuah kalimat. Karena posisinya sebagai subjek, kata ganti ini diletakkan di <strong>awal kalimat</strong> atau <strong>sebelum kata kerja (verb)</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Subject pronouns replace nouns that are the subject of a clause. They are placed before the verb.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Sedangkan <strong>object pronoun</strong> adalah kata ganti yang berfungsi sebagai penerima aksi (objek) dalam sebuah kalimat. Kata ganti ini diletakkan setelah <strong>kata kerja (verb)</strong> atau setelah <strong>kata depan (preposition)</strong> seperti <em>to, for, with, at, in,</em> dan lain-lain.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Object pronouns receive the action in a sentence. They are placed after verbs or prepositions.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Perubahan Subject ke Object Pronoun</h2>\r\n    <p>Berikut adalah tabel perubahan bentuk dari kata ganti subjek menjadi kata ganti objek yang harus dipahami agar tidak tertukar dalam struktur kalimat:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 1. Subject Pronoun vs Object Pronoun</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>Subject Pronoun (Sebelum Verb)</th>\r\n                <th>Object Pronoun (Setelah Verb / Preposition)</th>\r\n                <th>Arti / Makna</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>I</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>me</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Saya</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>You</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>you</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Kamu / Kalian</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>They</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>them</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Mereka</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>We</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>us</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Kami / Kita</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>He</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>him</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Dia (Laki-laki)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>She</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>her</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Dia (Perempuan)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>It</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>it</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Dia (Benda / Hewan)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Aturan Penggunaan dalam Kalimat</h2>\r\n    \r\n    <h3>1. Aturan Penempatan Subject Pronoun</h3>\r\n    <p>Ingatlah bahwa kata ganti subjek bertindak melakukan aksi. Struktur dasarnya adalah: <strong>[Subject Pronoun] + Verb</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>She</strong> loves cooking. <em>(Bukan: Her loves cooking)</em></li>\r\n            <li><strong>They</strong> built a new office last year. <em>(Bukan: Them built...)</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Aturan Penempatan Object Pronoun</h3>\r\n    <p>Kata ganti objek menerima aksi atau mengikuti kata depan. Struktur dasarnya adalah: <strong>Verb + [Object Pronoun]</strong> atau <strong>Preposition + [Object Pronoun]</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The teacher called <strong>him</strong>. <em>(Setelah Verb \"called\")</em></li>\r\n            <li>Mr. John bought a beautiful flower for <strong>her</strong>. <em>(Setelah Preposition \"for\")</em></li>\r\n            <li>We will go with <strong>them</strong> tomorrow. <em>(Setelah Preposition \"with\")</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Pola Jebakan pada Tes TOEFL (Common Errors)</h2>\r\n    <p>Sering kali dalam soal structure, penggunaan kedua pronoun ini sengaja ditukar posisinya (terutama jika subjek atau objeknya digabung menggunakan kata hubung <em>\"and\"</em>) untuk mengecoh Anda. Perhatikan baik-baik posisinya terhadap kata kerja.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh Salah (Incorrect):</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><u>Me</u> and my brother went to Bali. ❌ <em>(Seharusnya gunakan <strong>I</strong> karena posisinya sebelum verb \"went\")</em></li>\r\n            <li>The manager spoke to Anita and <u>he</u>. ❌ <em>(Seharusnya gunakan <strong>him</strong> karena berada setelah preposition \"to\")</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh Benar (Correct):</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>My brother and <strong>I</strong> went to Bali.  <em>(Correct)</em></li>\r\n            <li>The manager spoke to Anita and <strong>him</strong>.  <em>(Correct)</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 3, 1, '2026-06-16 12:36:26', '2026-06-16 14:52:28'),
(7, 5, 'POSSESSIVE PRONOUN', 'possessive-pronoun', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Possessive Pronouns - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .note-box {\r\n            background-color: #fffaf0;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #dd6b20;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 1: STRUCTURE (Part 4)</div>\r\n        <h1>D. POSSESSIVE PRONOUN</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Possessive pronouns</strong> merupakan kata yang digunakan untuk mengindikasikan bahwa sesuatu benda/hal itu merupakan milik seseorang atau juga memiliki hubungan dengan seseorang lainnya. Biasanya digunakan dalam kalimat yang disampaikan secara lisan maupun tulisan untuk menghindari pengulangan kata.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        What are Possessive Pronouns? Possessive pronouns are words used to indicate that something belongs to someone or has a relationship with another person. They are used to avoid repeating words.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Perhatikan contoh kalimat berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <em>“I had dinner with Jane and Jane’s brother, Michael.”</em><br>\r\n        Untuk menghindari pengulangan nama Jane dalam kalimat tersebut, kita dapat menggunakan possessive pronoun.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Pembagian Kelompok Kata Ganti Kepemilikan</h2>\r\n    <p>Kata ganti kepemilikan dibagi menjadi dua jenis utama, yaitu bentuk terikat (dependent) dan bentuk mandiri (independent):</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>1. Dependent Possessive Pronoun (Possessive Adjective)</h3>\r\n    <p>Aturan penggunaan <em>dependent possessive pronouns</em> adalah mereka wajib digunakan <strong>sebelum kata benda (noun)</strong>. Jenis kata ini bergantung pada keberadaan kata benda yang mengikutinya untuk menunjukkan kepemilikan atau hubungan langsung.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        The rule of dependent possessive pronouns is that they are used before a noun. They are dependent on the noun that comes after them to show ownership or a direct relationship.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Independent Possessive Pronoun (Possessive Absolute)</h3>\r\n    <p>Aturan penggunaan <em>independent possessive pronouns</em> adalah mereka biasanya diletakkan di <strong>akhir kalimat atau klausa</strong>, dan <strong>tidak boleh diikuti oleh kata benda (noun)</strong> setelahnya.</p>\r\n    <p>Namun, jenis kata ini membutuhkan informasi penjelas sebelumnya (*auxiliary information*) agar pembaca mengetahui benda apa yang sedang ditunjukkan kepemilikannya.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        The rule of independent possessive pronouns is that they normally come at the end of the sentence or clause, and they should not be followed by a noun. They need prior information to show what ownership is being indicated.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Perubahan Bentuk Kata Ganti Kepemilikan</h2>\r\n    <p>Berikut adalah klasifikasi perubahan bentuk lengkap sesuai dengan Table 4 pada buku panduan:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 4. Dependent-Independent Possessive Pronouns</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>Subject Pronoun</th>\r\n                <th>Dependent Possessive Pronoun / Possessive Adjective</th>\r\n                <th>Independent Possessive Pronoun / Possessive Absolute</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>I</strong></td>\r\n                <td>My</td>\r\n                <td>Mine</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>You (singl)</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Your (singl)</td>\r\n                <td>Yours (singl)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>He</strong></td>\r\n                <td>His</td>\r\n                <td>His</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>She</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Her</td>\r\n                <td>Hers</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>It</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Its</td>\r\n                <td>Its*</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>You (pl)</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Your (pl)</td>\r\n                <td>Yours (pl)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>We</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Our</td>\r\n                <td>Ours</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>They</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Their</td>\r\n                <td>Theirs</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"note-box\">\r\n        <strong>*Catatan Penting (Its):</strong> Penggunaan kata <em>its</em> sebagai independent possessive pronoun atau possessive absolute sangat jarang sekali digunakan. Bahkan ini hampir tidak pernah digunakan dalam Bahasa Inggris formal.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Contoh Penggunaan dalam Kalimat</h2>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Penggunaan Dependent (Diikuti Noun):</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>This is <strong>my book</strong>. <em>(Kata \"my\" menerangkan kata benda \"book\")</em></li>\r\n            <li>We will take <strong>our car</strong>. <em>(Kata \"our\" menerangkan kata benda \"car\")</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Penggunaan Independent (Tidak Diikuti Noun):</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>This book is <strong>mine</strong>. <em>(Bukan: This is mine book)</em></li>\r\n            <li>We will take our car or <strong>theirs</strong>. <em>(Kata \"theirs\" menggantikan frasa \"their car\" di akhir kalimat)</em></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 4, 1, '2026-06-16 13:00:41', '2026-06-16 14:52:35'),
(8, 6, 'ADJECTIVE AND ADVERB', 'adjective-and-adverb', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Adjective and Adverb - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .grammar-label {\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            font-size: 8.5pt;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            background-color: #e2e8f0;\r\n            padding: 1px 6px;\r\n            border-radius: 3px;\r\n            margin-right: 4px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 1: STRUCTURE (Part 5)</div>\r\n        <h1>E. ADJECTIVE AND ADVERB</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Biasanya di bagian <em>Structure and Written Expression</em> pada TOEFL, <strong>adjective</strong> digunakan untuk menggantikan <strong>adverb</strong> dan sebaliknya <strong>adverb</strong> digunakan untuk menggantikan <strong>adjective</strong>. Padahal kedua hal tersebut, yakni adjective dan adverb mempunyai fungsi penggunaan yang berbeda. Untuk itu, sangat penting memahami penggunaan adjective dan adverb.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>1. Adjective (Kata Sifat)</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Adjectives have only one job, they describe nouns or pronouns.\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Adjective hanya memiliki satu fungsi utama, yaitu menjelaskan kata benda (noun) atau kata ganti (pronoun).</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>She is a <strong>beautiful</strong> woman.<br>\r\n                <span class=\"grammar-label\">beautiful = ADJ</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">woman = NOUN</span><br>\r\n                <em>(Adjective \"beautiful\" menjelaskan kata benda \"woman\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">She is <strong>beautiful</strong>.<br>\r\n                <span class=\"grammar-label\">She = PRONOUN</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">beautiful = ADJ</span><br>\r\n                <em>(Adjective \"beautiful\" menjelaskan kata ganti \"She\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>2. Adverb (Kata Keterangan)</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Adverbs do three different things. They describe verbs, adjectives, or other adverbs.\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Berbeda dengan kata sifat, adverb dapat melakukan tiga tugas yang berbeda, yaitu menjelaskan kata kerja (verb), kata sifat (adjective), atau kata keterangan lainnya (adverb lain).</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Example:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>She sings <strong>beautifully</strong>.<br>\r\n                <span class=\"grammar-label\">sings = VERB</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">beautifully = ADV</span><br>\r\n                <em>(Adverb \"beautifully\" menjelaskan kata kerja \"sings\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">She is a <strong>beautifully</strong> dressed woman.<br>\r\n                <span class=\"grammar-label\">beautifully = ADV</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">dressed = ADJ</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">woman = NOUN</span><br>\r\n                <em>(Adverb \"beautifully\" menjelaskan adjective \"dressed\", di mana adjective tersebut berfungsi menjelaskan noun \"woman\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">She is a <strong>truly</strong> beautifully dressed woman.<br>\r\n                <span class=\"grammar-label\">truly = ADV</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">beautifully = ADV</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">dressed = ADJ</span> <span class=\"grammar-label\">woman = NOUN</span><br>\r\n                <em>(Adverb \"truly\" menjelaskan adverb \"beautifully\", di mana adverb \"beautifully\" tersebut menjelaskan adjective \"dressed\" yang sedang menerangkan noun \"woman\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Kesimpulan Penggunaan Dasar</h2>\r\n    <p>Maka, kesimpulan utama dari fungsi penggunaan adjective dan adverb ditunjukkan oleh tabel 5 berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 5. Basic Use of Adjective and Adverb</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>PART OF SPEECH</th>\r\n                <th>BASIC USE / FUNCTION</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>ADJECTIVE</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Adjectives describe <strong>nouns</strong> or <strong>pronouns</strong>.</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>ADVERB</strong></td>\r\n                <td>Adverbs describe <strong>verbs</strong>, <strong>adjectives</strong>, or <strong>other adverbs</strong>.</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 5, 1, '2026-06-16 13:08:01', '2026-06-16 14:52:42');
INSERT INTO `materials` (`id`, `category_id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `summary`, `audio_file`, `thumbnail`, `sort_order`, `is_published`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(10, 6, 'COORDINATE CONNECTOR', 'coordinate-connector', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Coordinate Connector - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .note-box {\r\n            background-color: #fffaf0;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #dd6b20;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 2: STRUCTURE (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>A. COORDINATE CONNECTOR</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Sebelum kita bahas tentang coordinate connector, sedikit kita ulas terlebih dahulu tentang klausa (clause). <strong>Klausa (clause)</strong> merupakan kumpulan kata yang terdiri dari satu <strong>subject</strong> dan satu <strong>verb</strong>. Clause dapat membentuk suatu kalimat (sentence).</p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Dan dalam satu kalimat dapat terdiri dari satu atau lebih klausa. Ketika dalam kalimat itu terdapat dua klausa, maka hal yang perlu untuk diperhatikan yakni:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Pertama, pastikan tiap <strong>subject</strong> ada <strong>verb</strong>-nya.</li>\r\n        <li>Tiap <strong>verb</strong> memiliki <strong>subject</strong>.</li>\r\n        <li>Kemudian, klausa-klausa tersebut harus dihubungkan dengan tepat, yakni salah satu caranya dengan menggunakan <strong>coordinate connector</strong>.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        A clause is a group of words containing a subject and a verb. A sentence can consist of one or more clauses. When there are two clauses in a sentence, they must be properly connected. Therefore, coordinate connectors are used to connect clauses in a sentence.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Jenis dan Fungsi Coordinate Connector</h2>\r\n    <p>Terdapat lima (5) jenis <em>coordinate connector</em> utama yang digunakan untuk menghubungkan dua klausa setara, seperti yang ditunjukkan pada tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 6. Coordinate Connector</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th style=\"width: 20%;\">Coordinate Connector</th>\r\n                <th>Function and Example</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>And</strong></td>\r\n                <td>To combine two clauses that have the same meaning or have the same position (setara).<br>\r\n                <em>e.g. Mom is cooking, <strong>and</strong> Dad is washing a car.</em><br>\r\n                (Ibu sedang memasak, dan Ayah sedang mencuci mobil)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>But</strong></td>\r\n                <td>To join two clauses that have opposite meaning (berlawanan).<br>\r\n                <em>e.g. Rani is tall, <strong>but</strong> Rini is short.</em><br>\r\n                (Rani tinggi, tetapi Rini pendek)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Or</strong></td>\r\n                <td>To combine two clauses that mean choice (pilihan).<br>\r\n                <em>e.g. You must eat your meal, <strong>or</strong> your brother will do it.</em><br>\r\n                (Kamu harus makan makananmu, atau saudaramu yang akan memakannya.)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>So</strong></td>\r\n                <td>To combine two clauses that mean cause and effect (sebab-akibat).<br>\r\n                <em>e.g. I was hungry, <strong>so</strong> I bought a big burger.</em><br>\r\n                (Saya lapar, jadi saya membeli sebuah burger yang besar.)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Yet</strong></td>\r\n                <td>The meaning is almost the same as <em>but</em>. <em>Yet</em> is used to connect two clauses that have contradictory meanings but are not actually contradictory as shown in <em>but</em> (tidak benar-benar bertentangan).<br>\r\n                <em>e.g. I am hungry, <strong>yet</strong> I am not going to eat.</em><br>\r\n                (Saya lapar, namun saya tidak akan makan.)</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"note-box\">\r\n        <strong>Catatan Penting (Pola Tanda Baca):</strong> Selalu gunakan tanda koma (<strong>,</strong>) tepat sebelum kata <em>coordinate connector</em> ditempatkan saat menghubungkan dua klausa independen.\r\n        <br><br>\r\n        <strong>Pola Dasar Kalimat:</strong><br>\r\n        <div style=\"font-family: monospace; font-size: 11pt; background: #fff; padding: 5px; border: 1px dashed #dd6b20; display: inline-block; margin-top: 5px;\">\r\n            Subject + Verb <strong>, [connector]</strong> Subject + Verb\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 6, 1, '2026-06-16 13:13:13', '2026-06-16 14:53:00'),
(11, 6, 'ADVERB CLAUSE CONNECTOR', 'adverb-clause-connector', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Adverb Clause Connector - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 9.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: center;\r\n            padding: 10px 8px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 8px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n            vertical-align: top;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 2: STRUCTURE (Part 2)</div>\r\n        <h1>C. ADVERB CLAUSE CONNECTOR</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Mari kita pahami terlebih dahulu tentang <em>adverb</em>, <em>adverb phrase</em>, dan <em>adverb clause</em> sebelum kita lanjut membahas <strong>adverb clause connector</strong>. Perhatikan perbedaan antara tiga tingkat penggunaan dalam kalimat berikut:</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Adverb:</strong> Mysha blew some balloons <u>yesterday</u>.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Adverb phrase:</strong> Mysha blew some balloons <u>before party</u>.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Adverb clause:</strong> Mysha blew some balloons <u>before she had a party</u>.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Kalimat dengan <em>adverb clause</em> berfungsi menggabungkan dua klausa, yakni klausa pertama <em>“Mysha blew some balloons”</em> dan klausa kedua <em>“she had a party”</em> dengan menggunakan kata hubung berupa <strong>adverb clause connector “before”</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        An adverb clause is a clause that functions as an adverb in a sentence. It contains a subject and a verb and is introduced by an adverb clause connector to join two clauses together.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Dua Bentuk Dasar Pola Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Kalimat yang memiliki <em>adverb clause</em> mempunyai dua bentuk dasar penulisan struktur posisi di dalam bahasa Inggris. Perhatikan peletakan klausa dan konektor berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>She gets good scores <strong>because</strong> she has been studying hard.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Because</strong> she has been studying hard<strong>,</strong> she gets good scores.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Dari kedua contoh di atas, terdapat dua klausa pada masing-masing kalimat, yaitu <em>“she gets good scores”</em> dan <em>“she has been studying hard”</em>. Klausa <em>“she has been studying hard”</em> merupakan bentuk <strong>adverb clause</strong> yang dikenali secara langsung dari penggunaan kata hubung (connector) <strong>“because”</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Pada <strong>kalimat pertama</strong>, connector berada di <u>tengah kalimat</u>, sehingga <strong>tidak terdapat tanda koma (,)</strong> yang digunakan.</li>\r\n        <li>Pada <strong>kalimat kedua</strong>, connector berada di <u>awal kalimat</u>. Dalam pola ini, ketika connector ditempatkan di awal, maka <strong>wajib dibutuhkan sebuah tanda koma (,)</strong> di tengah kalimat sebagai pemisah antar-klausa.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Adverb Clause Connector & Pola Dasar Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Berikut adalah daftar pembagian klasifikasi <em>adverb connector</em> yang lazim digunakan beserta visualisasi pola strukturnya sesuai dengan Tabel 7:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 7. Adverb Clause Connectors</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>TIME</th>\r\n                <th>CAUSE</th>\r\n                <th>CONDITION</th>\r\n                <th>CONTRAST</th>\r\n                <th>MANNER</th>\r\n                <th>PLACE</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>after<br>until<br>as<br>when<br>before<br>while<br>since<br>as soon as<br>as long as</td>\r\n                <td>because<br>since<br>that</td>\r\n                <td>if<br>whether<br>in case<br>provided<br>providing<br>unless</td>\r\n                <td>although<br>even though<br>though<br>while<br>whereas</td>\r\n                <td>as<br>in that</td>\r\n                <td>where<br>wherever</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Pola Penulisan Struktur Kalimat</h3>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #f7fafc; border-left: 4px solid #4a5568;\">\r\n        <strong>Pola 1: Connector di Tengah (Tanpa Koma)</strong>\r\n        <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n            Subject + Verb + <strong>[Adverb Connector]</strong> + Subject + Verb\r\n        </div>\r\n        <em>Example:</em> Mysha gets happy <strong>since</strong> she had a scholarship.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #f7fafc; border-left: 4px solid #4a5568;\">\r\n        <strong>Pola 2: Connector di Awal (Wajib Menggunakan Koma)</strong>\r\n        <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n            <strong>[Adverb Connector]</strong> + Subject + Verb <strong>, (comma)</strong> + Subject + Verb\r\n        </div>\r\n        <em>Example:</em> <strong>Since</strong> she had a scholarship<strong>,</strong> Mysha gets happy.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 7, 1, '2026-06-16 13:21:26', '2026-06-16 14:53:05'),
(12, 6, 'NOUN CLAUSE CONNECTOR', 'noun-clause-connector', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Noun Clause Connector - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n            vertical-align: top;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 2: STRUCTURE (Part 3)</div>\r\n        <h1>D. NOUN CLAUSE CONNECTOR</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Noun clause</strong> adalah klausa yang berfungsi sebagai kata benda (noun). Di dalam sebuah kalimat, noun clause digunakan sebagai objek dari kata kerja (object of a verb), objek dari kata depan (object of a preposition), atau sebagai subjek kalimat (subject of a sentence).</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        A noun clause is a clause that functions as a noun. In a sentence, it is used as the object of a verb, the object of a preposition, or the subject of a sentence.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Tiga Fungsi Penggunaan Posisi Noun Clause</h2>\r\n\r\n    <h3>1. Sebagai Object of a Verb (Objek Kata Kerja)</h3>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan contoh kalimat berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <em>“Mom knows <strong>when her daughter will come home</strong>.”</em>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Pada contoh di atas terdapat dua klausa, yaitu <em>“Mom knows”</em> dan <em>“her daughter will come home”</em>. Kedua klausa tersebut digabungkan menggunakan connector <strong>“when”</strong>. Kata hubung <em>when</em> mengubah klausa setelahnya menjadi sebuah noun clause yang berfungsi sebagai objek dari kata kerja <em>“knows”</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Sebagai Object of a Preposition (Objek Kata Depan)</h3>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan contoh kalimat berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <em>“Mom is concerned about <strong>when her daughter will come home</strong>.”</em>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Kalimat ini memiliki dua klausa yang juga digabungkan dengan kata hubung <strong>“when”</strong>. Di sini, <em>when</em> berfungsi mengubah klausa setelahnya menjadi sebuah noun clause yang bertindak sebagai objek yang mengikuti kata depan (preposisi) <strong>“about”</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>3. Sebagai Subject of a Sentence (Subjek Kalimat)</h3>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan contoh kalimat berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <em>“<strong>When her daughter will come home</strong> is very important.”</em>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Pola kalimat ini sedikit lebih sulit untuk dikenali dalam soal TOEFL. Klausa <em>“her daughter will come home”</em> yang digabungkan oleh connector <strong>“when”</strong> di awal kalimat bertindak penuh sebagai satu kesatuan subjek tunggal. Seluruh rangkaian klausa tersebut menjadi subjek bagi kata kerja utama berupa <strong>“is”</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Analisis Contoh Soal TOEFL (Example)</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fffaf0; border-left: 4px solid #dd6b20;\">\r\n        <strong>Soal:</strong><br>\r\n        <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</u> was late caused many problems.<br>\r\n        a. That he &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c. There<br>\r\n        b. The driver &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d. Because\r\n        <br><br>\r\n        <strong>Analisis & Jawaban:</strong><br>\r\n        Pada contoh di atas, terdapat dua kata kerja (verb) yaitu <strong>“was”</strong> dan <strong>“caused”</strong>, di mana masing-masing membutuhkan subjek. \r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Pilihan <strong>B</strong> salah karena <em>the driver</em> hanya menyediakan satu subjek saja.</li>\r\n            <li>Pilihan <strong>C</strong> dan <strong>D</strong> salah karena kata <em>there</em> dan <em>because</em> bukan berfungsi sebagai subjek.</li>\r\n            <li>Jawaban paling tepat adalah <strong>A (That he)</strong>, sehingga kalimatnya menjadi: <em>\"<strong>That he</strong> was late caused many problems.\"</em> Kata <em>\"he\"</em> bertindak sebagai subjek dari kata kerja <em>\"was\"</em>, dan seluruh kesatuan klausa <em>\"That he was late\"</em> bertindak menjadi subjek utama dari kata kerja <em>\"caused\"</em>.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Noun Clause Connector</h2>\r\n    <p>Beberapa kata hubung klausa benda yang lazim digunakan ditunjukkan pada tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 8. Noun Clause Connectors</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th style=\"width: 25%;\">Connector</th>\r\n                <th>Example & Meaning</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>What</strong></td>\r\n                <td>I know <strong>what</strong> you did last summer.<br><em>(Aku tahu apa yang kamu lakukan musim panas lalu)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Whatever</strong></td>\r\n                <td>You should not steal <strong>whatever</strong> the reason is.<br><em>(Kamu sebaiknya tidak mencuri apa pun alasannya)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>If</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>If</strong> you wanted to cook healthy food, I will help you with the recipes.<br><em>(Jika kamu ingin memasak makanan sehat, aku akan membantumu dengan resep-resepnya)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Whenever</strong></td>\r\n                <td><strong>Whenever</strong> you wanted to cook healthy food, I will help you with the recipes.<br><em>(Kapan pun kamu mau memasak masakan sehat, aku akan membantumu dengan resep-resepnya)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>That</strong></td>\r\n                <td>I don’t believe the story <strong>that</strong> he told me.<br><em>(Aku tidak percaya cerita yang ia katakan padaku)</em></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 8, 1, '2026-06-16 13:23:12', '2026-06-16 14:53:10'),
(13, 6, 'ADJECTIVE CLAUSE CONNECTOR', 'adjective-clause-connector', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Adjective Clause Connector - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h3 {\r\n            font-size: 11.5pt;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            margin-top: 20px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 9.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n            vertical-align: top;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .grammar-label {\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            font-size: 8.5pt;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            color: #e53e3e;\r\n            background-color: #fed7d7;\r\n            padding: 1px 5px;\r\n            border-radius: 3px;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 2: STRUCTURE (Part 4)</div>\r\n        <h1>E. ADJECTIVE CLAUSE CONNECTOR</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Sama halnya seperti klausa dependen lainnya, <strong>adjective clause</strong> membutuhkan paling sedikit satu <strong>subject</strong> dan satu <strong>verb</strong>. Adjective clause memiliki fungsi yang sama persis seperti kata sifat biasa (*adjective*), yaitu: menerangkan kata benda (*describe a noun*) baik berupa orang (*person*), tempat (*place*), maupun benda/hal (*thing*).</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Adjective clauses have the same function as an adjective: describe a noun (person, place, thing). Adjective clauses must go immediately after the noun they are describing.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Aturan Penempatan dalam Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Adjective clause wajib diletakkan <strong>tepat langsung setelah kata benda (noun) yang dijelaskannya</strong>. Oleh karena itu, klausa ini bisa muncul di tengah kalimat maupun di akhir kalimat, tergantung posisi benda penjelasnya.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Perhatikan dua bentuk posisi penempatan pada contoh berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>This is the book <u>which I bought yesterday</u>.<br>\r\n                <em>(Adjective clause berada di <strong>akhir kalimat</strong> karena menjelaskan kata benda \"the book\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">The man <u>who is standing over there</u> helped me.<br>\r\n                <em>(Adjective clause berada di <strong>tengah kalimat</strong> karena wajib mengikuti kata benda \"the man\")</em>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Catatan Penting Peran Ganda Kata Hubung</h2>\r\n    <p>Dalam beberapa pola kalimat, sebuah <em>adjective clause connector</em> dapat berperan ganda sekaligus dalam satu waktu, yaitu berfungsi sebagai <strong>connector sekaligus bertindak sebagai subject (C/S)</strong> dari klausa dependen tersebut. Ketentuan peran ganda ini berlaku khusus untuk kata hubung: <strong>who, which, dan that</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Klasifikasi Jenis Adjective Clause Connector</h2>\r\n    <p>Berikut adalah pembagian jenis kata hubung klausa sifat berdasarkan komponen acuan bendanya sesuai dengan Tabel 9:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 9. Adjective Clause Connectors</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th style=\"width: 25%;\">Connectors</th>\r\n                <th>Description & Structural Examples</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Who</strong><br><small style=\"color:#718096;\">(people)</small></td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    The man <span class=\"grammar-label\">who (C)</span> you <span class=\"grammar-label\">S</span> recommended <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span> was hired <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span> yesterday.<br>\r\n                    She needs a secretary <span class=\"grammar-label\">who (C/S)</span> can type <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span> fast.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Whom</strong><br><small style=\"color:#718096;\">(people/object & after prepositions)</small></td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    I found the man <span class=\"grammar-label\">whom (C)</span> you <span class=\"grammar-label\">S</span> recommended <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span>.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Which</strong><br><small style=\"color:#718096;\">(things)</small></td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    I like the book <span class=\"grammar-label\">which (C)</span> you <span class=\"grammar-label\">S</span> recommended <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span>.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>That</strong><br><small style=\"color:#718096;\">(people or things)</small></td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    The people <span class=\"grammar-label\">that (C/S)</span> were vaccinated <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span> did not get sick <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span>.<br>\r\n                    <small><em>*Note: Cannot be used after a preposition, or when the clause is between commas.</em></small>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Where</strong><br><small style=\"color:#718096;\">(places)</small></td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    I went to the restaurant <span class=\"grammar-label\">where (C)</span> you <span class=\"grammar-label\">S</span> went <span class=\"grammar-label\">V</span> last month.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Whose</strong><br><small style=\"color:#718096;\">(possessive)</small></td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    Digunakan untuk menunjukkan hubungan kepemilikan kata benda yang mengikutinya.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Pola Dasar Struktur Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Secara visual, struktur penyusunan kalimat ditandai oleh dua pola utama berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #f7fafc; border-left: 4px solid #4a5568;\">\r\n        <strong>Pola 1: Muncul di Akhir Kalimat</strong>\r\n        <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n            Subject + Verb + <strong>NOUN</strong> + [Adjective Connector] + Subject + Verb\r\n        </div>\r\n        <em>Example:</em> I like the book <strong>that</strong> you recommended.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #f7fafc; border-left: 4px solid #4a5568;\">\r\n        <strong>Pola 2: Muncul di Tengah Kalimat</strong>\r\n        <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n            Subject <strong>(NOUN)</strong> + [Adjective Connector] + Subject + Verb + Kata Kerja Utama (Verb)\r\n        </div>\r\n        <em>Example:</em> The man <strong>who</strong> you recommended was hired yesterday.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 9, 1, '2026-06-16 13:26:19', '2026-06-16 14:53:17'),
(14, 7, 'SUBJECT-VERB AGREEMENT', 'subject-verb-agreement', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Subject-Verb Agreement - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .grammar-marker {\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            text-decoration: underline;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>A. SUBJECT-VERB AGREEMENT</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Aturan dasar dari <strong>Subject-Verb Agreement</strong> adalah penyesuaian antara subjek dan kata kerja di dalam sebuah kalimat. Jika subjek berbentuk tunggal (*singular*), maka kata kerjanya juga harus tunggal. Sebaliknya, jika subjek berbentuk jamak (*plural*), maka kata kerjanya juga wajib berbentuk jamak.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Subject-verb agreement means that a singular subject needs a singular verb, and a plural subject needs a plural verb. They must match in number.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Aturan Dasar Kesesuaian (*Basic Agreement Rules*)</h2>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Untuk memahami perubahan bentuk kata kerja berdasarkan subjeknya, perhatikan ketentuan dasar di bawah ini:</p>\r\n\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th style=\"width: 25%;\">Subject Type</th>\r\n                <th style=\"width: 35%;\">Verb / Auxiliary Rule</th>\r\n                <th>Examples</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Singular Subject</strong><br><small>(He, She, It, Nama Orang, Benda Tunggal)</small></td>\r\n                <td>Kata kerja utama ditambah akhiran <strong>-s/-es</strong>.<br>Menggunakan to be/auxiliary: <strong>is, was, does, has</strong>.</td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    The <span class=\"grammar-marker\">student</span> <span class=\"grammar-marker\">walks</span> to school.<br>\r\n                    The <span class=\"grammar-marker\">car</span> <span class=\"grammar-marker\">is</span> expensive.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Plural Subject</strong><br><small>(They, We, You, Benda Jamak)</small></td>\r\n                <td>Kata kerja utama tetap pada bentuk dasar (<strong>tanpa -s/-es</strong>).<br>Menggunakan to be/auxiliary: <strong>are, were, do, have</strong>.</td>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    The <span class=\"grammar-marker\">students</span> <span class=\"grammar-marker\">walk</span> to school.<br>\r\n                    The <span class=\"grammar-marker\">cars</span> <span class=\"grammar-marker\">are</span> expensive.\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Hal yang Sering Mengecoh dalam TOEFL</h2>\r\n    <p>Pada soal TOEFL Written Expression, hubungan antara subjek dan kata kerja sering kali dibuat seolah-olah terpisah jauh atau terhalang oleh kata-kata lain agar peserta terkecoh. Kunci utamanya adalah selalu temukan <strong>subjek inti</strong> kalimat terlebih dahulu, lalu periksa apakah kata kerjanya sudah sesuai.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh Analisis:</strong>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><strong>Salah:</strong> The <u>key</u> to those rooms <b>are</b> missing.</li>\r\n            <li><strong>Benar:</strong> The <span class=\"grammar-marker\">key</span> to those rooms <span class=\"grammar-marker\">is</span> missing.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; font-size: 10pt; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n            *Analisis: Kata \"rooms\" berbentuk jamak, namun subjek inti dari kalimat tersebut adalah \"key\" (tunggal). Oleh karena itu, kata kerja bantunya harus menggunakan \"is\", bukan \"are\".\r\n        </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 10, 1, '2026-06-16 13:36:32', '2026-06-16 14:54:00');
INSERT INTO `materials` (`id`, `category_id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `summary`, `audio_file`, `thumbnail`, `sort_order`, `is_published`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(15, 7, 'AGREEMENT AFTER PREPOSITIONAL PHRASE', 'agreement-after-prepositional-phrase', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Agreement After Prepositional Phrase - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .error-text {\r\n            color: #e53e3e;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>B. AGREEMENT AFTER PREPOSITIONAL PHRASE</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Terkadang <strong>prepositional phrases</strong> (frasa kata depan, seperti: <em>in, on, at, of, to, by</em>) dapat hadir tepat di antara <strong>subject</strong> dan <strong>verb</strong>. Nah, jika <em>object of preposition</em>-nya berbentuk tunggal (*singular*) sedangkan subjeknya jamak (*plural*), atau sebaliknya, maka hal ini sering kali membingungkan kita dalam menentukan kesesuaian antara subjek dan kata kerjanya (*subject-verb agreement*).</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Sometimes a prepositional phrase comes between the subject and the verb. If the object of the preposition matches a different number format than the subject, it can lead to confusion in identifying the correct verb agreement.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Analisis Contoh Kesalahan Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan struktur dua contoh kalimat yang memuat kekeliruan (*error*) di bawah ini:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh 1 (SALAH):</strong><br>\r\n        The <u>key</u> [on the tables] <span class=\"error-text\">are</span> broken.<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(SINGULAR Subject + PLURAL Object of Preposition + PLURAL Verb)</small>\r\n        <br><br>\r\n        <strong>Analisis:</strong> Kita mungkin mengira bahwa <em>tables</em> merupakan subjeknya karena kata ini terletak tepat sebelum kata kerja <em>“are”</em>. Namun, <em>tables</em> bukanlah subjek melainkan <strong>object of the preposition “on”</strong>. Subjek asli dari kalimat tersebut adalah <strong>“key”</strong> (tunggal), maka kata kerjanya seharusnya menggunakan <strong>“is”</strong>.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh 2 (SALAH):</strong><br>\r\n        The <u>keys</u> [on the table] <span class=\"error-text\">is</span> broken.<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(PLURAL Subject + SINGULAR Object of Preposition + SINGULAR Verb)</small>\r\n        <br><br>\r\n        <strong>Analisis:</strong> Kita mungkin akan berpikir bahwa <em>table</em> merupakan subjek karena posisinya tepat berada di depan kata kerja <em>“is”</em>. Kita harus jeli mengenali bahwa <em>table</em> hanyalah berfungsi sebagai <strong>object of the preposition “on”</strong>. Karena sesungguhnya subjek utamanya adalah <strong>“keys”</strong> (jamak), maka kata kerjanya yang tepat seharusnya menggunakan <strong>“are”</strong>.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Rumus Dasar Kesesuaian Frasa Preposisi</h2>\r\n    <p>Guna menghindari jebakan ini, ikuti formula baku penulisan struktur kalimat yang dirangkum pada tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 10. Agreement with Prepositional Phrases</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>SUBJECT/VERB AGREEMENT WITH PREPOSITIONAL PHRASES</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>Subject</strong> + (prepositional phrase) + <strong>Verb</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        When a prepositional phrase comes between the subject and the verb, be sure that the verb agrees with the subject (bukan mengikuti objek dari kata depannya).\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 11, 1, '2026-06-16 13:38:08', '2026-06-16 14:54:11'),
(16, 7, 'AGREEMENT AFTER EXPRESSION OF QUALITY', 'agreement-after-expression-of-quality', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Agreement After Expression of Quality - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .label-type {\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            font-size: 8.5pt;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            background-color: #e2e8f0;\r\n            padding: 1px 6px;\r\n            border-radius: 3px;\r\n            margin-left: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>C. AGREEMENT AFTER EXPRESSION OF QUALITY</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Aturan kesesuaian (*subject-verb agreement*) selanjutnya yang harus diperhatikan yakni ketika subjek merupakan ungkapan dari suatu kuantitas (<strong>expression of quality/quantity</strong>) seperti: <strong>all, most, half, atau some</strong>, yang kemudian langsung diikuti oleh preposisi <strong>“of”</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Pada situasi khusus ini, kata penunjuk kuantitas tersebut tidak bisa berdiri sendiri menentukan bentuk kata kerjanya. Bentuk kata kerja (*verb*) apakah menjadi tunggal (*singular*) atau jamak (*plural*) ditentukan secara penuh oleh <strong>kata benda (noun) yang berada di dalam frasa setelah preposisi “of”</strong> tersebut.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        When the subject is an expression of quantity (such as all, most, half, or some) followed by the preposition \"of\", the verb must agree with the specific noun that follows the preposition \"of\".\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Tiga Aturan Kasus & Analisis Contoh</h2>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan variasi penentuan bentuk kata kerja melalui tiga contoh kalimat berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>1. Diikuti Singular Noun</strong><br>\r\n        All (of the <u>girl</u>) <strong>is</strong> very nice. <span class=\"label-type\">Singular</span>\r\n        <p style=\"margin: 5px 0 0 0; font-size: 10pt; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n            *Analisis: Karena kata benda yang mengikuti preposisi \"of\" berbentuk tunggal yaitu <em>\"girl\"</em>, maka kata kerjanya wajib berbentuk tunggal, yaitu <strong>\"is\"</strong>.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>2. Diikuti Plural Noun</strong><br>\r\n        All (of the <u>girls</u>) <strong>are</strong> very nice. <span class=\"label-type\">Plural</span>\r\n        <p style=\"margin: 5px 0 0 0; font-size: 10pt; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n            *Analisis: Karena kata benda yang mengikuti preposisi \"of\" berbentuk jamak yaitu <em>\"girls\"</em>, secara otomatis kata kerjanya wajib menyesuaikan menjadi jamak, yaitu <strong>\"are\"</strong>.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>3. Diikuti Uncountable Noun (Kata Benda Tak Dapat Dihitung)</strong><br>\r\n        All (of the <u>information</u>) <strong>was</strong> updated. <span class=\"label-type\">Uncountable</span>\r\n        <p style=\"margin: 5px 0 0 0; font-size: 10pt; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n            *Analisis: Karena kata benda yang mengikuti preposisi \"of\" merupakan kata benda yang tidak dapat dihitung yaitu <em>\"information\"</em>, maka kata kerja yang dibutuhkan wajib berbentuk tunggal, yaitu <strong>\"was\"</strong>.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Rumus Dasar Struktur Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Formula penulisan struktur kesesuaian ini dirangkum secara baku pada tabel di bawah ini:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 11. Agreement with Expression of Quality</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>SUBJECT/VERB AGREEMENT WITH EXPRESSION OF QUALITY</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>Subject (all, most, half, some)</strong> + (prepositional “of” + <strong>Noun</strong>) + <strong>Verb</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        *Rule: When the subject is an expression of quantity, followed by preposition “of”, the verb agrees on what follows the preposition “of”.\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 12, 1, '2026-06-16 13:39:07', '2026-06-16 14:54:19'),
(17, 7, 'AGREEMENT AFTER CERTAIN WORDS', 'agreement-after-certain-words', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Agreement After Certain Words - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #fff5f5;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n            vertical-align: top;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .word-grid {\r\n            display: grid;\r\n            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);\r\n            gap: 10px;\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            padding: 15px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            border-radius: 4px;\r\n            font-weight: 500;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>D. AGREEMENT AFTER CERTAIN WORDS</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Kata-kata tertentu (<strong>certain words</strong>) dalam bahasa Inggris secara aturan tata bahasanya (*grammatically*) <strong>selalu dianggap tunggal (singular)</strong>. Aturan ini tetap berlaku mutlak meskipun secara makna atau pengertian kontekstualnya kata-kata tersebut bisa saja memiliki kesan atau arti jamak (*plural*).</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        These words or expressions are grammatically singular, so they must always take singular verbs, even if they might sound plural in meaning.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Analisis Contoh Kesalahan</h2>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan contoh jebakan kalimat berikut yang sering muncul di lembar ujian:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh (SALAH):</strong><br>\r\n        Everything <span style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">are going</span> to be changed.<br><br>\r\n        <strong>Analisis & Perbaikan:</strong><br>\r\n        Walaupun secara makna kita memahami bahwa ada banyak hal/objek yang akan diubah (*everything* memberi kesan jamak), namun kata <em>everything</em> secara aturan tata bahasa adalah <strong>singular</strong>. Oleh karena itu, kata kerja jamak <em>\"are going\"</em> di atas keliru dan harus diubah menjadi kata kerja tunggal, yaitu <strong>\"is going\"</strong>.<br>\r\n        ➔ <strong>Benar:</strong> Everything <strong>is going</strong> to be changed.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Kata Tertentu Berstatus Tunggal</h2>\r\n    <p>Di bawah ini merupakan kelompok kata ganti tidak tentu (*indefinite pronouns*) dan penunjuk kuantitas satuan yang wajib dipasangkan dengan kata kerja tunggal:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"word-grid\">\r\n        <div>anybody</div>\r\n        <div>everybody</div>\r\n        <div>nobody</div>\r\n        <div>somebody</div>\r\n        <div>anyone</div>\r\n        <div>everyone</div>\r\n        <div>no one</div>\r\n        <div>someone</div>\r\n        <div>anything</div>\r\n        <div>everything</div>\r\n        <div>nothing</div>\r\n        <div>something</div>\r\n        <div style=\"grid-column: span 2;\">each (+ noun)</div>\r\n        <div style=\"grid-column: span 2;\">every (+ noun)</div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Rumus Dasar Struktur Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Sistem pengaplikasian pola kalimat ini dirangkum secara ringkas berdasarkan isi tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 12. Agreement After Certain Words</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>SUBJECT/VERB AGREEMENT AFTER CERTAIN WORDS</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>Subject (Certain Words)</strong> + <strong>Singular Verb</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        *Rule: When the subject is a certain word from the list above, the verb agrees on a singular verb.\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 13, 1, '2026-06-16 13:39:50', '2026-06-16 14:54:35'),
(18, 7, 'PARALLEL STRUCTURE', 'parallel-structure', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Parallel Structure - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: block;\r\n            margin: 10px 0;\r\n            text-align: center;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .error-badge {\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            font-size: 8.5pt;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            color: #e53e3e;\r\n            background-color: #fed7d7;\r\n            padding: 1px 5px;\r\n            border-radius: 3px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .correct-badge {\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            font-size: 8.5pt;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            color: #2f855a;\r\n            background-color: #c6f6d5;\r\n            padding: 1px 5px;\r\n            border-radius: 3px;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>E. PARALLEL STRUCTURE</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Dalam penggunaan bahasa Inggris yang baik, kita harus berupaya membuat unsur bahasa kita seseimbang mungkin. Keseimbangan inilah yang kemudian disebut dengan <strong>parallel structure</strong>. <em>Parallel Structure</em> dapat diartikan sebagai penggunaan pola kata yang sama untuk menunjukkan bahwa dua atau lebih pemikiran memiliki level kepentingan yang sama di dalam kalimat. Kita dapat mencapainya dengan membuat bentuk kata (*form of words*) semirip dan seimbang mungkin.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Parallel structure means using the same pattern of words to show that two or more ideas have the same level of importance. This can happen at the word, phrase, or clause level.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Analisis Dasar Keseimbangan Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Perhatikan contoh kalimat yang <strong>tidak parallel</strong> di bawah ini:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        Lisa loves <u>to sing</u> and <u>cooking</u>. <span class=\"error-badge\">TIDAK PARALLEL</span>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Secara mandiri, ungkapan <em>\"to sing\"</em> dan kata <em>\"cooking\"</em> adalah benar. Masalahnya muncul ketika keduanya digabungkan menggunakan kata hubung (*conjunction*) <strong>\"and\"</strong> padahal keduanya memiliki bentuk gramatikal yang berbeda. Kalimat tersebut dapat diperbaiki dengan dua cara agar seimbang:</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #f0fff4; border-left: 4px solid #38a169;\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Lisa loves <strong>to sing</strong> and <strong>to cook</strong>. <span class=\"correct-badge\">PARALLEL (Infinitive)</span></li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 6px;\">Lisa loves <strong>singing</strong> and <strong>cooking</strong>. <span class=\"correct-badge\">PARALLEL (Gerund)</span></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Ada beberapa situasi utama yang harus kita perhatikan dengan saksama di soal TOEFL terkait struktur paralel ini, yaitu:</p>\r\n    <ol style=\"padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 5px;\">\r\n        <li>Parallel structure dengan <strong>coordinate conjunctions</strong> (and, but, or).</li>\r\n        <li>Parallel structure dengan <strong>paired conjunctions</strong> (both...and, etc.).</li>\r\n        <li>Parallel structure dengan <strong>comparisons</strong> (perbandingan).</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <hr style=\"border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0; margin: 25px 0;\">\r\n\r\n    <h1>F. PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH COORDINATE CONJUNCTIONS</h1>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Tugas utama dari kata hubung koordinatif atau <strong>coordinate conjunctions (and, but, or)</strong> adalah menggabungkan ekspresi yang setara. Dengan kata lain, bentuk tata bahasa yang ada di salah satu sisi *coordinate conjunction* wajib parallel dengan apa yang ada di sisi lainnya. Kata hubung ini bisa menyatukan antar sesama <em>nouns, verbs, adjectives, phrases, subordinate clauses,</em> maupun <em>main clauses</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Pola Struktur Kata Hubung Koordinatif</h2>\r\n    <p>Aturan penyusunan berkait jumlah elemen yang dijajarkan dirangkum secara visual melalui pola dari tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 13. The Pattern of Parallel Structure with Coordinate Conjunctions</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH COORDINATE CONJUNCTIONS</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <p style=\"text-align: center; font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Pola untuk 2 Elemen:</p>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>(same structure)</strong> + and / but / or + <strong>(same structure)</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <p style=\"text-align: center; font-weight: 500; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Pola untuk Lebih dari 2 Elemen:</p>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>(same structure)</strong>, + <strong>(same structure)</strong>, + and / but / or + <strong>(same structure)</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <p style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568; margin-top: 15px; font-size: 9.5pt; text-align: center;\">\r\n                        \"The expression before and after the coordinate conjunction must be in the same structure.\"\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Contoh Penerapan Kalimat Seimbang</h2>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The report you are looking for could be <u>in the file</u> <strong>or</strong> <u>on the desk</u>.<br>\r\n                <small style=\"color: #4a5568;\">➔ <strong>Analisis:</strong> Seimbang karena menghubungkan sesama frasa tempat (Prepositional Phrase).</small>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">She works very hard <strong>but</strong> usually gets below-average grades.<br>\r\n                <small style=\"color: #4a5568;\">➔ <strong>Analisis:</strong> Seimbang karena menghubungkan sesama kata kerja (Verb) untuk subjek tunggal (works & gets).</small>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 14, 1, '2026-06-16 13:42:03', '2026-06-16 13:42:03'),
(19, 7, 'PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH COORDINATE CONJUNCTIONS', 'parallel-structure-with-coordinate-conjunctions', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Parallel Structure with Paired Conjunctions - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: block;\r\n            margin: 10px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .grid-paired {\r\n            display: grid;\r\n            grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);\r\n            gap: 10px;\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            border-radius: 4px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            text-align: center;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .error-highlight {\r\n            color: #e53e3e;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            text-decoration: line-through;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>G. PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH PAIRED CONJUNCTIONS</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Paired conjunctions</strong> merupakan kata hubung yang berpasangan di dalam bahasa Inggris. Kalimat yang memuat kata hubung berpasangan ini memiliki syarat mutlak, yaitu wajib menggunakan struktur kalimat yang sejajar (<strong>parallel structures</strong>) pada elemen-elemen yang dihubungkannya.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        The paired conjunctions require parallel structures. The expression between the first part and after the second part of the paired conjunction must be in the same grammatical structure.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Pasangan Kata Hubung Wajib (*The Pairs*)</h2>\r\n    <p>Berikut adalah pasangan baku kata hubung yang tidak boleh tertukar satu sama lain:</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"grid-paired\">\r\n        <div>both ... and</div>\r\n        <div>either ... or</div>\r\n        <div>neither ... nor</div>\r\n        <div>not only ... but also</div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Dua Jenis Kesalahan Utama dalam Soal TOEFL</h2>\r\n\r\n    <h3>1. Ketidaksejajaran Elemen Gramatikal (*Unparallel Elements*)</h3>\r\n    <p>Kesalahan terjadi saat bentuk kata di dalam pasangan tidak setara. Perhatikan contoh berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <strong>Salah:</strong> They want <u>either to go by motorcycle</u> <strong>or</strong> <u>by car</u>.<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #4a5568;\">*Analisis: Bagian pertama menggunakan frasa kata kerja \"to go by motorcycle\", sedangkan setelah \"or\" hanya frasa preposisi \"by car\".</small>\r\n        <br><br>\r\n        <strong>Opsi Perbaikan (Benar):</strong>\r\n        <ul style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">\r\n            <li>They want <strong>either to go by motorcycle or to go by car</strong>.</li>\r\n            <li>They want to go <strong>either by motorcycle or by car</strong>.</li>\r\n            <li>They want to go by <strong>either motorcycle or car</strong>.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Penggunaan Pasangan yang Salah (*Incorrect Pairs*)</h3>\r\n    <p>Kesalahan terjadi ketika kata hubung dipasangkan dengan kata lain yang bukan pasangan resminya. Perhatikan contoh berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>I need to buy both this novel <span class=\"error-highlight\">or</span> that one. ➔ (Seharusnya dipasangkan dengan <strong>and</strong>)</li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">Either Nay <span class=\"error-highlight\">nor</span> Lin is going to the party. ➔ (Seharusnya dipasangkan dengan <strong>or</strong>)</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Rumus Dasar Pasangan Sejajar</h2>\r\n    <p>Sistem penempatan struktur seimbang berdasarkan jenis kata hubungnya dirangkum secara visual pada tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 14. The Pattern of Parallel Structure with Paired Conjunctions</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH PAIRED CONJUNCTIONS</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n                        <strong>both</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>and</strong><br>\r\n                        <strong>either</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; + <strong>[same structure]</strong> + &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>or</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; + <strong>[same structure]</strong><br>\r\n                        <strong>neither</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>nor</strong><br>\r\n                        <strong>not only</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>but also</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568; font-size: 9.5pt;\">\r\n                        *Important Note: The expression between and after the paired conjunction must be in the same structure. So, it is a must for you to memorize the paired conjunctions!\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 15, 1, '2026-06-16 13:43:30', '2026-06-16 13:43:30');
INSERT INTO `materials` (`id`, `category_id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `summary`, `audio_file`, `thumbnail`, `sort_order`, `is_published`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(20, 7, 'PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH PAIRED CONJUNCTIONS', 'parallel-structure-with-paired-conjunctions', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Parallel Structure with Paired Conjunctions - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block ul {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding-left: 20px;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: block;\r\n            margin: 10px 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .grid-paired {\r\n            display: grid;\r\n            grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);\r\n            gap: 10px;\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            border-radius: 4px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            text-align: center;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .error-highlight {\r\n            color: #e53e3e;\r\n            font-weight: bold;\r\n            text-decoration: line-through;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 3: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 1)</div>\r\n        <h1>G. PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH PAIRED CONJUNCTIONS</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Paired conjunctions</strong> merupakan kata hubung yang berpasangan di dalam bahasa Inggris. Kalimat yang memuat kata hubung berpasangan ini memiliki syarat mutlak, yaitu wajib menggunakan struktur kalimat yang sejajar (<strong>parallel structures</strong>) pada elemen-elemen yang dihubungkannya.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        The paired conjunctions require parallel structures. The expression between the first part and after the second part of the paired conjunction must be in the same grammatical structure.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Pasangan Kata Hubung Wajib (*The Pairs*)</h2>\r\n    <p>Berikut adalah pasangan baku kata hubung yang tidak boleh tertukar satu sama lain:</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"grid-paired\">\r\n        <div>both ... and</div>\r\n        <div>either ... or</div>\r\n        <div>neither ... nor</div>\r\n        <div>not only ... but also</div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Dua Jenis Kesalahan Utama dalam Soal TOEFL</h2>\r\n\r\n    <h3>1. Ketidaksejajaran Elemen Gramatikal (*Unparallel Elements*)</h3>\r\n    <p>Kesalahan terjadi saat bentuk kata di dalam pasangan tidak setara. Perhatikan contoh berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <strong>Salah:</strong> They want <u>either to go by motorcycle</u> <strong>or</strong> <u>by car</u>.<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #4a5568;\">*Analisis: Bagian pertama menggunakan frasa kata kerja \"to go by motorcycle\", sedangkan setelah \"or\" hanya frasa preposisi \"by car\".</small>\r\n        <br><br>\r\n        <strong>Opsi Perbaikan (Benar):</strong>\r\n        <ul style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">\r\n            <li>They want <strong>either to go by motorcycle or to go by car</strong>.</li>\r\n            <li>They want to go <strong>either by motorcycle or by car</strong>.</li>\r\n            <li>They want to go by <strong>either motorcycle or car</strong>.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Penggunaan Pasangan yang Salah (*Incorrect Pairs*)</h3>\r\n    <p>Kesalahan terjadi ketika kata hubung dipasangkan dengan kata lain yang bukan pasangan resminya. Perhatikan contoh berikut:</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>I need to buy both this novel <span class=\"error-highlight\">or</span> that one. ➔ (Seharusnya dipasangkan dengan <strong>and</strong>)</li>\r\n            <li style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">Either Nay <span class=\"error-highlight\">nor</span> Lin is going to the party. ➔ (Seharusnya dipasangkan dengan <strong>or</strong>)</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Rumus Dasar Pasangan Sejajar</h2>\r\n    <p>Sistem penempatan struktur seimbang berdasarkan jenis kata hubungnya dirangkum secara visual pada tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 14. The Pattern of Parallel Structure with Paired Conjunctions</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>PARALLEL STRUCTURE WITH PAIRED CONJUNCTIONS</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n                        <strong>both</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>and</strong><br>\r\n                        <strong>either</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; + <strong>[same structure]</strong> + &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>or</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; + <strong>[same structure]</strong><br>\r\n                        <strong>neither</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>nor</strong><br>\r\n                        <strong>not only</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>but also</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568; font-size: 9.5pt;\">\r\n                        *Important Note: The expression between and after the paired conjunction must be in the same structure. So, it is a must for you to memorize the paired conjunctions!\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 16, 1, '2026-06-16 13:43:59', '2026-06-16 13:43:59'),
(21, 8, 'PRESENT AND PAST PARTICIPLE', 'present-and-past-participle', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Present and Past Participle - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        tr:nth-child(even) {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 4: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 2)</div>\r\n        <h1>A. PRESENT AND PAST PARTICIPLE</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Participle</strong> merupakan kata yang terbentuk dari penyatuan bentuk dasar kata kerja (<em>base form of verb</em>) dengan akhiran (<em>suffix</em>) tertentu. Terdapat dua jenis utama <em>participle</em> berdasarkan bentuk akhirannya:</p>\r\n    \r\n    <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 15px;\">\r\n        <li><strong>Present Participle:</strong> Dibentuk dengan menambahkan akhiran <strong>-ing</strong> pada kata kerja dasar.</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Past Participle:</strong> Dibentuk dengan menambahkan akhiran <strong>-ed</strong> atau <strong>-d</strong> pada kata kerja beraturan (*regular verb*). Namun, jika kata kerjanya tidak beraturan (*irregular verb*), maka perubahan bentuknya tidak konsisten.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        A participle is a word formed from a verb base that can function as a verb element or as a modifier (verbal). Present participles end in \"-ing\", while regular past participles end in \"-ed\" or \"-d\". Irregular past participles have inconsistent forms.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Lima Bentuk Umum Kata Kerja (*Verb Forms*)</h2>\r\n    <p>Pada dasarnya, sebuah kata kerja di dalam bahasa Inggris terbagi ke dalam lima bentuk utama. Perhatikan perubahan bentuknya pada tabel klasifikasi di bawah ini:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 15. Forms of Verb</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>Base Form</th>\r\n                <th>Present Tense</th>\r\n                <th>Past Tense</th>\r\n                <th>Present Participle</th>\r\n                <th>Past Participle</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Drink</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Irregular)</small></td>\r\n                <td>Drinks</td>\r\n                <td>Drank</td>\r\n                <td>Drinking</td>\r\n                <td>Drunk</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><strong>Play</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Regular)</small></td>\r\n                <td>Plays</td>\r\n                <td>Played</td>\r\n                <td>Playing</td>\r\n                <td>Played</td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Fungsi Participle Sebagai Kata Kerja (*Used as Verb*)</h2>\r\n    <p>Di dalam penggunaannya, *participle* dapat berfungsi ganda, yaitu sebagai <strong>verb</strong> (kata kerja utama) maupun sebagai <strong>verbal</strong> (kata sifat yang dibentuk dari kata kerja). Ketika diposisikan atau digunakan sebagai sebuah <strong>verb</strong>, aturan mekanismenya adalah sebagai berikut:</p>\r\n    \r\n    <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\r\n        <li><strong>Present Participle:</strong> Wajib digunakan bersama dengan kata kerja bantu (<em>auxiliary verb</em>, seperti komponen *be*) untuk membentuk aspek kalimat berkelanjutan (<em>continuous tense</em>).</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Past Participle:</strong> Digunakan bersama kata kerja bantu untuk membentuk aspek kalimat selesai (<em>perfect tense</em>) maupun struktur kalimat pasif (<em>passive voice</em>).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 17, 1, '2026-06-16 13:45:32', '2026-06-16 13:45:32'),
(22, 8, 'PAST PARTICIPLE AFTER HAVE', 'past-participle-after-have', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Participle Sebagai Verb dan Verbal - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #ebf8ff;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 8px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 4: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 2)</div>\r\n        <h1>A. PRESENT & PAST PARTICIPLE (PART 2: VERB VS VERBAL)</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Perbedaan mendasar yang sering memicu kekeliruan dalam soal TOEFL struktur kalimat (*Written Expression*) adalah ketidakmampuan membedakan kapan <em>participle</em> bertindak sebagai predikat atau kata kerja utama (<strong>Verb</strong>) dan kapan ia hanya bertindak sebagai penjelas kata benda (<strong>Verbal/Adjective</strong>).</p>\r\n\r\n    <h2>1. Participle Digunakan Sebagai Verb (*Kata Kerja Utama*)</h2>\r\n    <p>Ketika <em>present participle (-ing)</em> atau <em>past participle (-ed/-v3)</em> berfungsi sebagai kata kerja sejati dalam kalimat, mereka <strong>wajib didahului oleh kata kerja bantu (*auxiliary verb*)</strong> seperti bentuk <em>be (am, is, are, was, were)</em> atau bentuk <em>have (has, have, had)</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh Kalimat:</strong><br>\r\n        * The boy <strong>is playing</strong> in the yard. <span style=\"color:#3182ce;\">(Present Participle membentuk Continuous Tense)</span><br>\r\n        * The juice <strong>was drunk</strong> by Tony. <span style=\"color:#3182ce;\">(Past Participle membentuk Passive Voice)</span>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 16. Participle Used as Verb</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>PARTICIPLE USED AS VERB PATTERN</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        Subject + <strong>Auxiliary Verb (Be / Have)</strong> + <strong>Participle (Present/Past)</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        *Rule: A participle functions as a verb ONLY when it is accompanied by an auxiliary verb to complete the tense or passive construction.\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h2>2. Participle Digunakan Sebagai Verbal (*Kata Sifat / Modifiers*)</h2>\r\n    <p>Ketika digunakan sebagai <strong>Verbal</strong>, <em>participle</em> tidak berfungsi sebagai predikat melainkan murni bertindak sebagai kata sifat (*adjective*) yang menerangkan kata benda (*noun*). Ciri utamanya adalah <strong>tidak didahului oleh auxiliary verb</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 15px;\">\r\n        <li><strong>Present Participle sebagai Verbal:</strong> Bermakna aktif (melakukan aksi).</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Past Participle sebagai Verbal:</strong> Bermakna pasif (dikenai aksi).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #f7fafc; border-left: 4px solid #4a5568;\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh Kalimat:</strong><br>\r\n        * The boy <u>playing</u> in the yard is my brother. <span style=\"color:#4a5568;\">(Anak laki-laki <strong>yang sedang bermain</strong>...)</span><br>\r\n        * The juice <u>drunk</u> by Tony was fresh. <span style=\"color:#4a5568;\">(Jus <strong>yang diminum</strong> oleh Tony...)</span>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table 17. Participle Used as Verbal</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>PARTICIPLE USED AS VERBAL PATTERN</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        Subject + <strong>Participle (No Auxiliary)</strong> + ... + Main Verb\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        *Rule: When a participle stands alone without any auxiliary verb, it functions as an adjective (verbal) that describes a noun.\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 18, 1, '2026-06-16 13:46:08', '2026-06-16 13:46:08'),
(23, 8, 'PRESENT OR PAST PARTICIPLE AFTER BE', 'present-or-past-participle-after-be', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Past Participle After Have - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #fff5f5;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n            vertical-align: top;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 4: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 2)</div>\r\n        <h1>B. PAST PARTICIPLE AFTER HAVE</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Di dalam pengerjaan soal tata bahasa Inggris (khususnya bagian <em>Written Expression</em> pada tes TOEFL), salah satu aturan mutlak yang sering diuji adalah penggunaan kata kerja setelah turunan kata kerja bantu <strong>HAVE</strong>. Kapan pun kata bantu <em>have</em> digunakan, kata kerja utama yang mengikutinya harus berupa bentuk <strong>Past Participle (Verb 3)</strong> untuk menyatakan makna aktif \"sudah/telah\" (*Perfect Tense*).</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        Whenever you see any form of the auxiliary verb HAVE (have, has, had, having), you must ensure that the main verb that follows it is in the past participle form (Verb 3).\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Bentuk-Bentuk Turunan HAVE</h2>\r\n    <p>Aturan penyelarasan ini berlaku untuk seluruh variasi bentuk dari kata kerja bantu berikut:</p>\r\n    <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 15px;\">\r\n        <li><strong>Have / Has</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Present Perfect)</small></li>\r\n        <li><strong>Had</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Past Perfect)</small></li>\r\n        <li><strong>Having</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Perfect Participle)</small></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Analisis Contoh Kesalahan di Lembar Ujian</h2>\r\n    <p>Jebakan soal sering kali menaruh bentuk kata kerja dasar (*base form*) atau bentuk lampau kedua (*past tense*) setelah kata bantu *HAVE*. Perhatikan contoh berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Contoh (SALAH):</strong><br>\r\n        They have <span style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">drink</span> the water.* <small style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">(Base form setelah have)</small><br>\r\n        They have <span style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">drank</span> the water.* <small style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">(Verb 2 / Past tense setelah have)</small><br><br>\r\n        <strong>Analisis & Perbaikan:</strong><br>\r\n        Karena kalimat di atas menggunakan kata kerja bantu <em>\"have\"</em>, kata kerja berikutnya tidak boleh menggunakan bentuk dasar (*drink*) maupun bentuk kedua (*drank*). Kata kerja tersebut wajib diubah ke bentuk kata kerja ketiga atau *past participle*, yaitu <strong>\"drunk\"</strong>.<br>\r\n        ➔ <strong>Benar:</strong> They have <strong>drunk</strong> the water.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Pola Rumus Struktur Kalimat</h2>\r\n    <p>Aturan dasar kombinasi kata kerja bantu *have* dirangkum secara ringkas pada format tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table: Past Participle Structure After Have</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>VERB COMBINATION AFTER HAVE</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>have / has / had / having</strong> + <strong>Past Participle (Verb 3)</strong>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        *Rule: Do not use a base form or a simple past tense verb after any form of have. It must always be followed by a past participle.\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 19, 1, '2026-06-16 13:47:37', '2026-06-16 13:47:37'),
(24, 8, 'BASE FORM VERB AFTER MODALS', 'base-form-verb-after-modals', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"id\">\r\n<head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n    <title>Materi Present or Past Participle After Be - Poppins Font</title>\r\n    <style>\r\n        /* Mengambil font Poppins langsung dari Google Fonts */\r\n        @import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght=0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap\');\r\n\r\n        @page {\r\n            size: A4;\r\n            margin: 20mm 15mm;\r\n            background-color: #ffffff;\r\n            @bottom-right {\r\n                content: counter(page);\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n            @bottom-left {\r\n                content: \"Structure & Written Expression — TOEFL Equivalent\";\r\n                font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n                font-size: 9pt;\r\n                color: #718096;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        *, *::before, *::after {\r\n            box-sizing: border-box;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        body {\r\n            font-family: \'Poppins\', sans-serif;\r\n            color: #2d3748;\r\n            line-height: 1.6;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 10px;\r\n            font-size: 10.5pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .header-container {\r\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-bottom: 10px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 25px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .chapter-title {\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            text-transform: uppercase;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h1 {\r\n            font-size: 20pt;\r\n            color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            margin: 5px 0 0 0;\r\n            font-weight: 700;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        h2 {\r\n            font-size: 14pt;\r\n            color: #2c5282;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n            padding-left: 10px;\r\n            margin-top: 25px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        p {\r\n            margin-top: 0;\r\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\r\n            text-align: justify;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        strong {\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .bilingual-box {\r\n            background-color: #f7fafc;\r\n            border-right: 3px solid #cbd5e0;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            font-style: italic;\r\n            color: #4a5568;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        .example-block {\r\n            background-color: #f0fff4;\r\n            border-left: 4px solid #38a169;\r\n            padding: 12px 15px;\r\n            margin: 15px 0;\r\n            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        .pattern-box {\r\n            font-family: monospace;\r\n            font-size: 11pt;\r\n            background: #fff;\r\n            padding: 10px 15px;\r\n            border: 1px dashed #2b6cb0;\r\n            display: inline-block;\r\n            margin-top: 5px;\r\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        table {\r\n            width: 100%;\r\n            border-collapse: collapse;\r\n            margin: 20px 0;\r\n            font-size: 10pt;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        th {\r\n            background-color: #2b6cb0;\r\n            color: white;\r\n            font-weight: 600;\r\n            text-align: left;\r\n            padding: 10px 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #2b6cb0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        td {\r\n            padding: 12px;\r\n            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\r\n            font-weight: 400;\r\n            vertical-align: top;\r\n        }\r\n    </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"header-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"chapter-title\">CHAPTER 4: WRITTEN EXPRESSIONS (Part 2)</div>\r\n        <h1>C. PRESENT OR PAST PARTICIPLE AFTER BE</h1>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <p>Bentuk kata kerja bantu <strong>BE</strong> memiliki variasi yang sangat banyak di dalam bahasa Inggris. Ketika sebuah kata kerja bantu <em>be</em> diikuti langsung oleh kata kerja utama di dalam sebuah kalimat, maka hanya ada dua kemungkinan bentuk kata kerja yang diizinkan, yaitu bentuk <strong>Present Participle (-ing)</strong> atau bentuk <strong>Past Participle (-ed / V3)</strong>.</p>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"bilingual-box\">\r\n        An auxiliary verb BE can be followed by another verb in only two ways: a present participle (-ing) to form the active continuous tense, or a past participle (-ed/V3) to form the passive voice.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Daftar Variasi Bentuk BE</h2>\r\n    <p>Aturan penyelarasan partisipe ini berlaku mutlak bagi seluruh kata bantu di bawah ini:</p>\r\n    <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 15px;\">\r\n        <li><strong>am, is, are</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Present)</small></li>\r\n        <li><strong>was, were</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Past)</small></li>\r\n        <li><strong>be</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(After modals / to-infinitive)</small></li>\r\n        <li><strong>been</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(After have / perfect form)</small></li>\r\n        <li><strong>being</strong> <small style=\"color: #718096;\">(Continuous passive)</small></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Dua Fungsi Utama Penggunaan Setelah BE</h2>\r\n\r\n    <h3>1. Diikuti Present Participle (-ing) ➔ Makna Aktif</h3>\r\n    <p>Kombinasi ini digunakan untuk menyatakan perbuatan yang sedang berlangsung (*Continuous Tense*).</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\">\r\n        <strong>Benar:</strong> We <strong>are doing</strong> our homework.<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #4a5568;\">➔ Pola aktif: Subjek melakukan tindakan.</small>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h3>2. Diikuti Past Participle (V3) ➔ Makna Pasif</h3>\r\n    <p>Kombinasi ini digunakan untuk menyatakan kalimat pasif (*Passive Voice*), di mana subjek dikenai tindakan.</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #ebf8ff; border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;\">\r\n        <strong>Benar:</strong> The homework <strong>was done</strong> by us.<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #4a5568;\">➔ Pola pasif: Subjek menerima tindakan.</small>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2 style=\"color: #e53e3e; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">Analisis Jebakan Soal TOEFL</h2>\r\n    <p>Dalam bagian <em>Written Expression</em>, kesalahan fatal yang sering dimunculkan adalah meletakkan kata kerja dasar (*base form*) atau kata kerja lampau bentuk kedua (*simple past*) setelah komponen <em>BE</em>.</p>\r\n    <div class=\"example-block\" style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;\">\r\n        <strong>Salah:</strong> They were <span style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">take</span> the test.*<br>\r\n        <strong>Salah:</strong> They were <span style=\"color: #e53e3e; font-weight: bold;\">took</span> the test.*<br>\r\n        <small style=\"color: #718096;\">*Analisis: Bentuk \"take\" (base form) dan \"took\" (Verb 2) tidak boleh diposisikan langsung setelah \"were\". Kalimat aktif ini harus menggunakan present participle.</small><br>\r\n        ➔ <strong>Perbaikan yang Benar:</strong> They were <strong>taking</strong> the test.\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <h2>Pola Rumus Kombinasi Kata Kerja</h2>\r\n    <p>Skema penggabungan bentuk kata kerja setelah komponen <em>BE</em> dirangkum pada tabel berikut:</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Table: Participle Form Structures After BE</h3>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <thead>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <th>VERB COMBINATION AFTER BE</th>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </thead>\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>BE</strong> + <strong>Present Participle (-ing)</strong> ➔ <span style=\"font-size: 9.5pt; font-family: \'Poppins\';\">Makna Aktif</span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br>\r\n                    <div class=\"pattern-box\">\r\n                        <strong>BE</strong> + <strong>Past Participle (Verb 3)</strong> ➔ <span style=\"font-size: 9.5pt; font-family: \'Poppins\';\">Makna Pasif</span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <span style=\"font-style: italic; color: #4a5568;\">\r\n                        *Rule: Never use a base form verb or a simple past verb directly after any auxiliary verb BE.\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', NULL, NULL, 20, 1, '2026-06-16 13:48:28', '2026-06-16 13:48:28'),
(25, 1, 'Strategi Part A: Fokus pada Pembicara Kedua', 'strategi-part-a-fokus-pembicara-kedua', '<h2>Kenapa Pembicara Kedua Penting?</h2><p>Dalam bagian <strong>Short Conversations</strong>, audio biasanya memutar percakapan singkat antara dua orang (pria dan wanita), diikuti oleh satu pertanyaan. Nah, rahasia terbesarnya adalah: <strong>Kunci jawaban hampir selalu terletak pada pernyataan orang kedua.</strong></p><h3>Contoh Kasus:</h3><p><em>Man: Billy really made a big mistake this time.</em><br><em>Woman: Yes, he forgot to turn in his research paper.</em><br><em>Question: What does the woman say about Billy?</em></p><p>Pernyataan wanita (pembicara kedua) menyatakan bahwa Billy lupa mengumpulkan tugas. Maka, kamu harus mencari opsi jawaban yang maknanya paling mirip (restatement) dengan pernyataan tersebut.</p><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Tips:</strong> Saat mendengarkan percakapan, kamu boleh sedikit rileks saat orang pertama bicara, tapi <strong>harus sangat fokus</strong> saat orang kedua merespons.</div>', 'Pelajari mengapa jawaban untuk soal Part A sering kali berada pada kalimat yang diucapkan oleh pembicara kedua.', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 03:07:01', '2026-06-17 03:07:01'),
(26, 1, 'Strategi Part A: Hindari Suara yang Mirip', 'strategi-part-a-hindari-suara-mirip', '<h2>Jebakan Suara Mirip (Similar Sounds)</h2><p>Salah satu trik paling sering digunakan oleh pembuat soal TOEFL ITP adalah meletakkan kata-kata pada pilihan jawaban yang pelafalannya (suaranya) mirip dengan apa yang kamu dengar di audio, namun maknanya sama sekali berbeda.</p><h3>Contoh Kasus:</h3><p><em>Woman: Why couldn\'t Mark come with us?</em><br><em>Man: He was searching for a new <strong>apartment</strong>.</em></p><p>Pilihan Jawaban:<br>A. He was in the <strong>department</strong>.<br>B. He was looking for a place to live.<br>C. He was working on his <strong>research</strong>.<br>D. He had an <strong>appointment</strong>.</p><p>Perhatikan kata <em>department</em> dan <em>appointment</em> memiliki rima suara yang mirip dengan <em>apartment</em>. Ini adalah jebakan! Jawaban yang benar adalah B, yang merupakan <strong>makna ulang (restatement)</strong> tanpa menggunakan kata yang sama persis.</p><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Ingat!</strong> Jika sebuah pilihan jawaban terdengar terlalu mirip dengan kata di audio, hindari pilihan tersebut!</div>', 'Ketahui jebakan umum di TOEFL di mana pilihan jawaban yang terdengar mirip biasanya adalah jawaban yang salah.', NULL, NULL, 2, 1, '2026-06-17 03:07:01', '2026-06-17 03:07:01'),
(27, 2, 'Strategi Part B: Antisipasi Topik & Pertanyaan', 'strategi-part-b-antisipasi-topik', '<h2>Bagaimana Cara Mengantisipasi Topik?</h2><p>Di Part B (Long Conversations), kamu akan mendengarkan percakapan yang jauh lebih panjang dari Part A. Sangat penting bagi kamu untuk memanfaatkan jeda waktu dengan membaca pilihan jawaban (A, B, C, D) di lembar soal.</p><h3>Langkah-langkah:</h3><ol><li><strong>Gunakan Waktu Jeda:</strong> Saat narator membacakan instruksi, segera baca sekilas (skim) pilihan jawaban dari beberapa soal yang berkaitan dengan percakapan berikutnya.</li><li><strong>Cari Kata Kunci Berulang:</strong> Jika pilihan jawaban sering menyebutkan kata seperti <em>virus, vaccine, immune system</em>, kamu sudah tahu percakapan ini tentang biologi/kesehatan.</li><li><strong>Dengarkan Kalimat Pertama:</strong> Kalimat pertama sering kali berisi topik utama atau ide pokok dari keseluruhan percakapan.</li></ol><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Tips Tambahan:</strong> Jawaban atas pertanyaan-pertanyaan di Part B selalu berurutan dengan alur informasi di dalam audio.</div>', 'Cara efektif memprediksi topik pembicaraan sebelum mendengarkan audio Long Conversations.', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 03:07:01', '2026-06-17 03:07:01'),
(28, 3, 'Strategi Part C: Memahami Ide Pokok Ceramah', 'strategi-part-c-ide-pokok-ceramah', '<h2>Mencari Main Idea di Lectures</h2><p>Part C berisi ceramah atau monolog akademik (sejarah, sains, seni, dll). Pertanyaan pertama yang ditanyakan hampir selalu tentang gagasan utama (Main Idea) atau tujuan pembicaraan (Topic).</p><h3>Cara Menjawab:</h3><p>Berbeda dengan percakapan biasa, dosen atau pembicara dalam ceramah akademik biasanya langsung menyatakan tujuan mereka di <strong>dua atau tiga kalimat pertama</strong>.</p><ul><li>Perhatikan frasa pembuka seperti: <em>\"Today, we will be discussing...\"</em> atau <em>\"In this lecture, I\'m going to explain...\"</em>.</li><li>Pilihan jawaban yang benar biasanya tidak terlalu spesifik (detail) dan tidak terlalu umum.</li></ul><p>Fokuslah 100% pada bagian awal audio untuk mengamankan poin di pertanyaan nomor satu dari setiap ceramah!</p>', 'Tips mencari inti atau main idea dari sebuah ceramah akademik di Part C.', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 03:07:01', '2026-06-17 03:07:01'),
(29, 9, 'Strategi Main Idea: Baca Kalimat Pertama', 'strategi-main-idea-baca-kalimat-pertama', '<h2>Menemukan Main Idea dengan Cepat</h2><p>Pertanyaan tentang gagasan utama (<em>Main Idea</em>, <em>Primary Topic</em>, <em>Main Subject</em>) hampir selalu muncul sebagai pertanyaan pertama untuk setiap teks bacaan (passage).</p><h3>Strategi Jitu: Skimming</h3><p>Dalam teks akademik berbahasa Inggris, penulis biasanya meletakkan gagasan utama di <strong>kalimat pertama</strong> setiap paragraf. Oleh karena itu, strategi terbaiknya adalah:</p><ol><li>Baca <strong>kalimat pertama</strong> dari masing-masing paragraf di dalam teks.</li><li>Hubungkan kalimat-kalimat pertama tersebut untuk menarik satu kesimpulan umum.</li><li>Pilih jawaban yang merupakan rangkuman (restatement) dari kalimat-kalimat pertama tersebut.</li></ol><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Peringatan!</strong> Pilihan jawaban yang salah biasanya mengandung informasi yang hanya benar untuk satu paragraf saja (terlalu spesifik), atau malah membahas hal di luar teks (terlalu umum).</div>', 'Pelajari cara cepat menemukan gagasan utama (main idea) dari sebuah paragraf akademik tanpa harus membaca seluruh teks.', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 05:49:49', '2026-06-17 05:49:49'),
(30, 10, 'Strategi Vocabulary: Tebak Makna dari Konteks', 'strategi-vocabulary-tebak-makna-konteks', '<h2>Menebak Arti Kata Sulit</h2><p>Pertanyaan <em>Vocabulary in Context</em> menguji kemampuanmu memahami arti kata atau frasa tertentu berdasarkan kalimat di mana kata itu berada.</p><h3>Cara Menjawab:</h3><p>Sangat normal jika kamu tidak tahu arti kata tersebut! Pembuat soal sering menggunakan kata yang tidak umum, namun mereka selalu memberikan <strong>petunjuk (context clues)</strong> di kalimat yang sama atau kalimat sebelumnya/sesudahnya.</p><ul><li><strong>Petunjuk Definisi:</strong> Kata sulit sering kali langsung didefinisikan setelah tanda baca koma, garis miring, atau kata <em>\"is\" / \"means\" / \"or\"</em>.</li><li><strong>Petunjuk Lawan Kata (Contrast):</strong> Perhatikan kata hubung seperti <em>\"but\", \"however\", \"in contrast\"</em>. Makna kata tersebut berlawanan dengan ide di bagian kalimat lainnya.</li></ul><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Langkah Eksekusi:</strong> Gantikan kata sulit di teks dengan pilihan jawaban A, B, C, D. Pilihan mana yang membuat kalimat tersebut paling masuk akal secara keseluruhan? Itulah jawabannya!</div>', 'Jangan panik jika menemukan kosa kata sulit. Gunakan kalimat di sekitarnya sebagai petunjuk untuk menebak maknanya.', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 05:49:49', '2026-06-17 05:49:49');
INSERT INTO `materials` (`id`, `category_id`, `title`, `slug`, `content`, `summary`, `audio_file`, `thumbnail`, `sort_order`, `is_published`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(31, 11, 'Strategi Detail: Teknik Scanning Teks', 'strategi-detail-teknik-scanning', '<h2>Mencari Informasi Spesifik (Stated Details)</h2><p>Pertanyaan ini menanyakan informasi spesifik yang memang tertulis secara jelas (eksplisit) di dalam teks. Pertanyaannya sering diawali dengan <em>\"According to the passage...\"</em> atau <em>\"It is indicated in the passage that...\"</em>.</p><h3>Langkah-langkah Scanning:</h3><ol><li><strong>Tentukan Kata Kunci:</strong> Pilih kata kunci unik dari pertanyaan (misalnya: tahun, nama orang, lokasi, atau istilah spesifik).</li><li><strong>Scan Teks:</strong> Gerakkan mata dengan cepat dari atas ke bawah untuk mencari kata kunci tersebut di dalam teks (atau sinonimnya).</li><li><strong>Baca Kalimat Tersebut:</strong> Setelah menemukan kata kuncinya, bacalah seluruh kalimat yang memuat kata kunci tersebut dengan saksama.</li></ol><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Tips Cepat:</strong> Urutan soal biasanya mengikuti urutan paragraf! Soal detail nomor 2 kemungkinan besar jawabannya ada setelah jawaban untuk soal nomor 1.</div>', 'Cara menjawab soal detail (Stated Detail) dengan teknik memindai teks tanpa membuang waktu.', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 05:49:49', '2026-06-17 05:49:49'),
(32, 12, 'Strategi Reference: Menelusuri Kata Ganti', 'strategi-reference-menelusuri-kata-ganti', '<h2>Pronoun Reference (Rujukan Kata Ganti)</h2><p>Soal tipe ini biasanya berbentuk: <em>\"The word \'they\' in line 5 refers to...\"</em>. Inti dari soal ini adalah mencari kata benda asli (Noun) yang digantikan oleh Pronoun tersebut.</p><h3>Strategi Jawab:</h3><p>Karena tata bahasa Inggris mendikte bahwa kata ganti benda harus disebutkan <strong>setelah</strong> benda aslinya disebutkan, maka langkah pertamamu adalah:</p><ul><li>Temukan kata ganti (pronoun) yang ditanyakan di dalam teks.</li><li>Baca kalimat tepat <strong>sebelum</strong> pronoun tersebut berada (berjalan mundur).</li><li>Cari kata benda (noun) yang cocok secara tata bahasa. Jika pronounnya <em>\"they\"</em> (jamak), cari kata benda jamak. Jika <em>\"it\"</em> (tunggal), cari kata benda tunggal.</li></ul><div class=\"tip-box\"><strong>Verifikasi:</strong> Masukkan kata benda yang kamu pilih untuk menggantikan pronoun di teks asli. Apakah maknanya menjadi masuk akal? Jika ya, itu adalah jawaban yang tepat!</div>', 'Langkah pasti untuk menjawab soal rujukan kata (pronoun reference) seperti \"it\", \"they\", atau \"which\".', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2026-06-17 05:49:49', '2026-06-17 05:49:49');

